npc/guntur: The money is only the first thing this place takes. The rest is quieter, and worse.
npc/guntur: I've watched it hollow people out. First the sleep goes — up at 3 AM chasing a loss, heart pounding at every spin.
npc/guntur: Then the shame. They lie to the people they love. They hide the debt, the losses, the hours. The lying eats them from the inside.
npc/guntur: Then the anxiety that never switches off. The depression. The days you can't get out of bed because the number on the screen is all you can think about.
npc/guntur: Families break. Jobs vanish. And in the worst cases — the ones no statistic fully counts — people stop being able to see any way out at all.
npc/guntur: That is the real damage. Online gambling doesn't just empty your account. It attacks your mind, your relationships, your reason to keep going.
npc/guntur: If you feel that darkness closing in — on you, or someone you love — please hear this: it is not the end of the story, and you do not have to carry it alone.
npc/guntur: Help is real. Reaching for it is the bravest move you'll ever make. We'll talk about where to find it, past the core.
